Gastroenteritis (Stomach Flu):

• Gastroenteritis is also known as stomach flu
• The condition refers to the inflammation of the stomach or the intestine

Symptoms to look for:

• Abdominal cramps
• Severe stomach pain
• Diarrhoea
• Vomiting
• Fever

Causes:

• Ingestion of bacteria through:
   o Consumption of contaminated food
   o Contact with an infected person
   o Eating uncooked vegetables and fruits

